attachments.title: Bringing Verizon into Minecraft.
attachments.text: Believe it or not, until recently it was impossible to order a pizza from Minecraft. In fact, you couldn’t make a phone call, send a text message or browse the web from the game even if you built a phone. Verizon endeavored to solve these problems by building a phone in Minecraft that can actually connect to the real world without leaving the game. With the help of Wieden+Kennedy and BlockWorks, we built custom functionality that lets players browse the Internet, make video calls and create a selfie stick to send an MMS selfie to a friend. Minecraft experts such as SethBling and CaptainSparklez joined to beta test these features and show how they would use a working phone in the game
